  "prompt": "What type of plastic works best as roller chain tensioner?",
  "response": "For roller chain tensioners, typically high-performance plastics like:\n\n1. Delrin (Polyoxymethylene/POM)\n- High wear resistance\n- Low friction\n- Good mechanical strength\n- Commonly used in chain guide applications\n\n2. Nylon (Polyamide)\n- Good toughness\n- Self-lubricating\n- Wear-resistant\n- Handles moderate loads\n\n3. UHMW Polyethylene (Ultra-High Molecular Weight)\n- Excellent wear resistance\n- Low coefficient of friction\n- Good impact strength\n- Used in heavy-duty applications\n\n4. PEEK (Polyether Ether Ketone)\n- High temperature resistance\n- Superior mechanical properties\n- Excellent wear characteristics\n- More expensive\n\nThe best choice depends on specific application requirements like load, speed, temperature, and environmental conditions. Delrin is often considered the most versatile and cost-effective option for many roller chain tensioner designs.",
